                        "name": "pencil",
                        "displayName": "Nils Caspar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Pleas fix this ASAP",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=pencil",
                        "name": "pencil",
                        "displayName": "Nils Caspar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-01T05:05:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-01T05:05:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33678",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thamacher",
                        "name": "thamacher",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Hamacher",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The suggested patch from Nils is broken. As far as i can see the logic should be the same as in the Element::getValue() method. I've added a proper patch.\n\nAs a workaround you can derive the MultiCheckbox and implement the _getErrorMessages() method on your own, until the error is fixed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thamacher",
                        "name": "thamacher",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Hamacher",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-20T06:28:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-20T06:28:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34007",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=njcalugar",
                        "name": "njcalugar",
                        "displayName": "Nicholas Calugar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Here is a code snippet that shows a very similar issue that occurs when adding a custom error message to a multi select. In this case, _getErrorMessages returns an array with an extra dimension, which causes a Warning when the FormErrors View Helper tries to escape each error message:\n\n<?php\nset_include_path(get_include_path() . PATH_SEPARATOR . 'library');\n\ninclude('Zend\/Form\/Element\/Multiselect.php');\ninclude('Zend\/View.php');\ninclude('Zend\/Version.php');\n\necho (\"Zend_Version: \" . Zend_Version::VERSION . \"\\n\\n\");\n\necho \"PRINTING CONTROL ELEMENT:\\n\\n\";\n\n$control = new Zend_Form_Element_Multiselect('control');\n\n$control->addMultiOptions(\n\tarray(\n\t\t1 => 'One',\n\t\t2 => 'Two',\n\t\t3 => 'Three',\n\t)\n);\n\n$control->isValid(array(1,4));\n\necho $control->render(new Zend_View());\n\necho \"\\n\\nPRINTING BUG ELEMENT:\\n\\n\";\n\n$bug = new Zend_Form_Element_Multiselect('bug');\n\n$bug->addMultiOptions(\n\tarray(\n\t\t1 => 'One',\n\t\t2 => 'Two',\n\t\t3 => 'Three',\n\t)\n);\n\n$bug->addErrorMessage('%value% is invalid');\n\n$bug->isValid(array(1,4));\n\necho $bug->render(new Zend_View());\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=njcalugar",
                        "name": "njcalugar",
                        "displayName": "Nicholas Calugar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-27T10:02:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-27T10:02:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35117",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=pencil",
                        "name": "pencil",
                        "displayName": "Nils Caspar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Any news on this?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=pencil",
                        "name": "pencil",
                        "displayName": "Nils Caspar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-08T04:36:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-08T04:36:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35241",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The report and diagnosis are both incorrect. What happens is that the FormErrors view helper fails because the value passed to escape() is an array, not a string.\r\n\r\nWhat needs to be done is to flatten the errors within _getErrorMessages() so that we don't get multiple error messsages per validator.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-15T12:54:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-15T12:54:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35242",
                    "author": {
